headline: Is Disney a No-Brainer Buy? 3 Things It Still Has to Prove.
summary: Disney (NYSE: DIS) released fiscal first-quarter earnings on Wednesday morning, and the market responded with a loud "meh."  After all, its streaming business is now profitable, and it fully owns Hulu.  It's also set to launch the flagship ESPN streaming service in the fall.

headline: Disney Is Spending $60 Billion on Experiences: History Says It's the Right Move That Will Pay Off Years From Now.
summary: Investors certainly know Walt Disney (NYSE: DIS) as the media and entertainment powerhouse that owns popular cable networks including ABC, The Disney Channel, FX, and ESPN.  The business also has a budding streaming division that is starting to report positive operating income.  Management has announced a massive $60 billion investment, double the original plan, for the experiences division over the next decade.
